      "replicate_weights_used": null,
      "weight_variable_name": "SCIWGT",
      "weight_fields_interpretation": "The study uses TIMSS 2019 Grade 8 Science microdata and extracts student, teacher, and curriculum variables using the IEA IDB Analyzer and SPSS. The analytic sample is restricted to 44 countries/regions after data cleaning, yielding 309,511 remaining entries. For weighting, the authors explicitly use the science teacher weight (SCIWGT) because the key process-dimension variables (e.g., instructional clarity, instructional strategies, homework and experiment-related items) are reported by science teachers, and the focus is on curriculum effects from an instructional perspective. The manuscript does not report the use of replicate weights (e.g., BRR/jackknife), and it does not state that student weights were applied; instead, teacher weights are used to reduce sampling bias for teacher-reported covariates."
    },
